00:37:14.204 --> 00:37:17.062
"Wow, you have a very pretty pelvis!"

778
00:37:17.093 --> 00:37:18.499
That's what he said.

779
00:37:18.524 --> 00:37:20.273
I laughed out loud at that remark.

780
00:37:20.343 --> 00:37:25.241
I wasn't trying to be funny,
but one time during a TV show,

781
00:37:25.281 --> 00:37:27.124
the floor was slippery
and I fell backwards.

782
00:37:27.172 --> 00:37:28.679
- I suffered a concussion.
- Who did?

783
00:37:28.718 --> 00:37:29.882
I did!

784
00:37:29.922 --> 00:37:32.796
I was unconscious for a few seconds.

785
00:37:32.843 --> 00:37:36.643
People were worried about me,
so I went to take an X-ray.

786
00:37:36.726 --> 00:37:39.491
The doctor said this after
seeing the X-ray photo.

787
00:37:39.515 --> 00:37:41.601
He's been a doctor for 20 years.

788
00:37:41.633 --> 00:37:44.546
He said I had the biggest
skull he's ever seen.

789
00:37:44.578 --> 00:37:46.671
It filled up the whole screen!

790
00:37:48.309 --> 00:37:49.671
(Still baffled)

791
00:37:49.703 --> 00:37:52.210
It didn't even fit on the screen!

792
00:37:52.265 --> 00:37:55.030
I realized that it wasn't that I was
fat, but my skull itself is big!

793
00:37:55.077 --> 00:37:56.718
It didn't fit the screen!

794
00:37:56.743 --> 00:37:58.585
Corners were cut off.

795
00:37:58.610 --> 00:38:00.765
My face didn't fit.

796
00:38:00.906 --> 00:38:02.687
It was really amazing.

797
00:38:02.712 --> 00:38:03.937
So amazing!

798
00:38:04.047 --> 00:38:09.374
I heard that an industry expert in Japan
said that you'd take 10 years to get big?

799
00:38:09.422 --> 00:38:13.788
Back then, not along of singers
sang live on stage in Korea.

800
00:38:13.929 --> 00:38:18.030
I wasn't prepared to perform
on stage while singing live.

801
00:38:18.055 --> 00:38:21.750
I did a showcase in Japan, but every
singer in Japan sang live on stage.

802
00:38:21.803 --> 00:38:25.663
So for the first time ever, I
totally ruined a performance.

803
00:38:25.695 --> 00:38:28.804
I developed stage fright since then.

804
00:38:28.820 --> 00:38:30.507
I still have that a little.

805
00:38:30.828 --> 00:38:32.679
BoA's scared to be on stage?

806
00:38:32.695 --> 00:38:34.249
It's terrible.

807
00:38:34.289 --> 00:38:38.187
It's like saying Kyung-hoon's got a
fear of singing with his head-voice.

808
00:38:38.212 --> 00:38:41.062
Or Ho-dong having a
fear of dumpling soups.

809
00:38:41.087 --> 00:38:42.773
I get it right away!

810
00:38:42.867 --> 00:38:45.499
After that failure in Japan,

811
00:38:45.547 --> 00:38:48.132
I realized that I had to become
good at it no matter what.

812
00:38:48.164 --> 00:38:49.593
So I kept practicing.

813
00:38:49.648 --> 00:38:54.132
I was really determined,
I'd sing on tread mills,

814
00:38:54.226 --> 00:38:57.679
and every dance practice. I'd sing.

815
00:38:57.851 --> 00:38:59.452
How popular were you in Japan?

816
00:38:59.500 --> 00:39:00.757
When you were active?

817
00:39:00.781 --> 00:39:03.663
One of the things I'm sad about is that

818
00:39:03.725 --> 00:39:07.499
while I was really popular and while
things were going well for me,

819
00:39:07.539 --> 00:39:10.472
I never actually had a
moment to realize it.

820
00:39:10.497 --> 00:39:13.616
You might've been too young and busy.

821
00:39:13.828 --> 00:39:15.702
Kids these days might not know, but

822
00:39:15.734 --> 00:39:18.421
when BoA was really big,

823
00:39:18.461 --> 00:39:20.945
her news weren't really on
the entertainment page.

824
00:39:21.008 --> 00:39:23.406
Her successes were shown on the front line!

825
00:39:23.468 --> 00:39:25.593
She had unprecedented level of success.

826
00:39:25.687 --> 00:39:27.945
Because she was that big of a hit?

827
00:39:29.065 --> 00:39:31.859
Yeah, she'd be on the news and
the newscaster would say,

828
00:39:31.914 --> 00:39:34.616
"BoA's done it again!"

829
00:39:34.688 --> 00:39:36.687
"Our BoA made us proud in Japan!"

830
00:39:36.735 --> 00:39:38.703
We'd hear that often on the news.

831
00:39:38.728 --> 00:39:41.757
It was very significant considering
that Japan has the second-biggest

832
00:39:41.781 --> 00:39:44.203
music market in the world.

833
00:39:44.266 --> 00:39:47.250
That was when Hikaru Utada was #1 in Japan.

834
00:39:47.313 --> 00:39:51.398
No one was able to topple
her in Japan but BoA.

835
00:39:51.485 --> 00:39:54.968
- Who?
- Itadakimasu? [Thanks for food]

836
00:39:56.218 --> 00:40:00.000
(Hikaru Utada, not Itadakimasu!)

837
00:40:02.538 --> 00:40:05.125
I'm sure she enjoyed her meal too.

838
00:40:07.774 --> 00:40:10.843
This one's about what happened on stage.

839
00:40:10.883 --> 00:40:14.078
One time, I was singing a slow
song and I broke out in tears.

840
00:40:14.103 --> 00:40:15.914
I couldn't finish the song.

841
00:40:15.953 --> 00:40:20.875
It was so touching though, the fans
finished the song for me by singing along.

842
00:40:20.938 --> 00:40:26.492
What do you think my manager
said when I got off the stage?

843
00:40:26.960 --> 00:40:28.453
A Japanese manager?

844
00:40:28.508 --> 00:40:31.648
A Korean manager, but we were in Japan.

845
00:40:31.688 --> 00:40:33.906
She came up to you while you
were still crying and said,

846
00:40:33.945 --> 00:40:36.515
"BoA, I love you."

847
00:40:37.514 --> 00:40:39.922
You should really date someone.

848
00:40:39.977 --> 00:40:41.750
It's about time.

849
00:40:42.625 --> 00:40:45.148
You've been wanting to say "I
love you" to someone for so long?

850
00:40:45.485 --> 00:40:48.070
I think Jang-hoon's suffering
from lack of affection.

851
00:40:48.149 --> 00:40:51.312
(This giant is short on affection)

852
00:40:51.375 --> 00:40:54.086
I know this for sure, I
know her manager, Eun-ha.

853
00:40:54.149 --> 00:40:56.773
She's not so warm and fuzzy.

854
00:40:56.836 --> 00:40:59.093
"You cried because you forgot the lyrics?"

855
00:40:59.117 --> 00:41:00.781
No!

856
00:41:00.977 --> 00:41:03.945
She is my drinking buddy,
best friend, and a manager.

857
00:41:04.016 --> 00:41:06.820
Act it out, come down stage as you cry.

858
00:41:06.903 --> 00:41:08.437
Walk over there?

859
00:41:10.778 --> 00:41:12.378
Stop!

860
00:41:12.760 --> 00:41:14.360
(The end)

861
00:41:14.594 --> 00:41:16.382
(That was all?)

862
00:41:17.020 --> 00:41:18.620
(Yeah, that was all)

863
00:41:19.259 --> 00:41:22.375
Who says it's still Kang Ho-dong's era?

864
00:41:22.725 --> 00:41:25.195
I really looked forward
to your answer right now.

865
00:41:25.924 --> 00:41:28.023
I was looking forward to it too!

866
00:41:29.984 --> 00:41:32.609
It was my 10th anniversary concert.

867
00:41:32.679 --> 00:41:35.609
The last song of the
concert was "Merr-Chri."

868
00:41:35.687 --> 00:41:41.039
It was released in Japan over 13 years ago,

869
00:41:41.078 --> 00:41:44.625
but it's still played
every Christmas season.

870
00:41:44.672 --> 00:41:48.656
I still sing it in Japan at awards shows.

871
00:41:48.680 --> 00:41:54.218
As soon as I started singing the
song, I thought of my past 10 years.

872
00:41:54.258 --> 00:41:56.609
I saw those moments like a movie scene.

873
00:41:56.617 --> 00:41:58.726
I was so sad.

874
00:41:58.891 --> 00:42:03.211
And I couldn't sing the song, and
my fans sang the song for me there.

875
00:42:03.297 --> 00:42:07.117
I've never heard Japanese
audience sing that loudly before.

876
00:42:08.000 --> 00:42:10.312
"BoA, your fans are
better singers than you!"

877
00:42:10.337 --> 00:42:11.851
That would've been better.

878
00:42:11.882 --> 00:42:13.773
- It was harsher?
- Yeah.

879
00:42:13.938 --> 00:42:17.023
The fans sang the song till the end.

880
00:42:17.062 --> 00:42:22.445
I was so thankful and moved,
and came down the stage.

881
00:42:24.953 --> 00:42:29.570
"Hey BoA, you got paid for
not doing any work at all!"

882
00:42:29.820 --> 00:42:32.562
"A professional should
finish singing on stage."

883
00:42:32.617 --> 00:42:35.422
"How could you cry and not finish?"

884
00:42:35.445 --> 00:42:37.554
It wasn't that long, just a short phrase.

885
00:42:37.610 --> 00:42:41.211
She said this to me while she
was also wiping away her tears.

886
00:42:41.314 --> 00:42:43.234
"This is a broadcasting accident!"

887
00:42:43.266 --> 00:42:44.281
Not it.

888
00:42:45.477 --> 00:42:48.554
"BoA, let's record the song
again in this version!"

889
00:42:48.633 --> 00:42:49.492
No.

890
00:42:49.563 --> 00:42:50.953
"Let's publish it."

891
00:42:50.969 --> 00:42:52.289
- DVD?
- Yeah, DVD.

892
00:42:52.352 --> 00:42:55.836
That comes out after every concert,
we were filming that day too.

893
00:42:55.961 --> 00:42:58.172
"BoA, you should've finished."

894
00:42:58.430 --> 00:42:59.797
You're close!

895
00:43:01.022 --> 00:43:03.625
"BoA, that felt great! Do an encore!"

896
00:43:03.650 --> 00:43:05.336
It wasn't quite an encore.

897
00:43:05.375 --> 00:43:06.617
Not an encore.

898
00:43:06.656 --> 00:43:09.539
But Ho-dong was very close.

899
00:43:10.360 --> 00:43:12.539
"Let's do another slow song!"

900
00:43:12.641 --> 00:43:14.241
"BoA, do it again."

901
00:43:15.266 --> 00:43:17.047
Sang-min's got it!

902
00:43:17.094 --> 00:43:18.929
"Go on stage again!"

903
00:43:19.016 --> 00:43:21.648
"BoA, let's sing that one again."

904
00:43:21.945 --> 00:43:25.047
"We're filming for your DVD today,
we can't use this version."

905
00:43:25.078 --> 00:43:27.297
"Go up and sing it properly,
and we'll use that take."

906
00:43:27.352 --> 00:43:30.078
She would say that! That's her style.

907
00:43:30.103 --> 00:43:32.304
(In disbelief)

908
00:43:34.169 --> 00:43:36.711
What's funny is that she
was crying herself, too.

909
00:43:36.765 --> 00:43:39.351
Her eyes were all red but said,

910
00:43:39.383 --> 00:43:42.226
"We can't use this version,
go and sing again."

911
00:43:42.289 --> 00:43:43.929
She was still thinking with reason!

912
00:43:43.977 --> 00:43:46.007
So what happened after was that...

913
00:43:46.024 --> 00:43:48.023
She had to keep her cool.

914
00:43:48.055 --> 00:43:50.140
I said, "What?"

915
00:43:53.301 --> 00:43:55.195
(She was trying not to explode in anger)

916
00:43:55.343 --> 00:43:58.968
I'd say it's a more valuable take.

917
00:43:59.304 --> 00:44:00.562
Listen to me, Jang-hoon!

918
00:44:00.578 --> 00:44:02.178
Sorry.

919
00:44:02.955 --> 00:44:05.851
I thought you were done after that noise.

920
00:44:06.281 --> 00:44:09.461
I grabbed the mic and went up on
stage again while I was still mad.

921
00:44:09.485 --> 00:44:11.265
I went up on stage and told the audience,

922
00:44:11.305 --> 00:44:13.093
"My manager's making me
sing because of the DVD..."

923
00:44:13.133 --> 00:44:14.757
You told on her?

924
00:44:14.860 --> 00:44:16.664
You're scary too!

925
00:44:16.689 --> 00:44:18.336
(The two won't lose to each other)

926
00:44:18.383 --> 00:44:21.586
But they're still really good friends!
The best of friends.

927
00:44:22.437 --> 00:44:24.890
So I finally sang the song
properly until the end.

928
00:44:24.906 --> 00:44:27.125
I'm sure they were even
more moved to see that.

929
00:44:27.156 --> 00:44:29.961
They did like it, they
got to hear it again.

930
00:44:29.977 --> 00:44:32.172
It was a very happy moment.

931
00:44:32.211 --> 00:44:35.570
Then a few months later, I was
given the DVD of that concert.

932
00:44:35.586 --> 00:44:37.398
The finished product.

933
00:44:37.594 --> 00:44:40.515
Finally, "Merry-Chri" was coming on.

934
00:44:40.617 --> 00:44:42.968
And the girl in the DVD is crying!

935
00:44:42.993 --> 00:44:45.179
They must've liked that moment!

936
00:44:45.946 --> 00:44:48.843
And it showed the whole
song that I was crying on.

937
00:44:48.891 --> 00:44:50.922
Then comes a bonus material!

938
00:44:50.961 --> 00:44:53.228
My second take on the song was it!

939
00:44:53.684 --> 00:44:57.461
("Merry-Chri" performance of
her 10th anniversary concert)

940
00:45:04.701 --> 00:45:07.898
(She thought of her memories
from the past 10 years)

941
00:45:09.350 --> 00:45:12.132
(She couldn't stop crying
because she was so emotional)

942
00:45:13.292 --> 00:45:17.664
(The fans started to lift up
their voices to sing for her)

943
00:45:24.140 --> 00:45:26.375
Thank you very much everyone!

944
00:45:28.015 --> 00:45:31.273
(BoA exits the stage after this
happy moment shared with her fans)

945
00:45:31.392 --> 00:45:34.445
(But the video continues on)

946
00:45:34.649 --> 00:45:36.812
(A moment later...)

947
00:45:36.906 --> 00:45:39.570
(She comes on stage again
at her fans' cheers)

948
00:45:40.484 --> 00:45:43.179
(This DVD ended up with both versions!)

949
00:45:43.767 --> 00:45:45.726
She had a big picture planned!

950
00:45:45.774 --> 00:45:46.992
How smart of her!

951
00:45:47.031 --> 00:45:48.812
Nothing was taken out!

952
00:45:48.898 --> 00:45:50.498
She's really smart.

953
00:45:50.711 --> 00:45:53.289
How should I say it...
I was really moved.

954
00:45:53.297 --> 00:45:55.039
And I was very grateful.

955
00:45:55.602 --> 00:45:57.648
That's what I was feeling.

956
00:45:57.680 --> 00:46:00.297
I was thinking about how
happy I was at the moment.

957
00:46:00.336 --> 00:46:03.578
And she totally destroyed with her words.

958
00:46:03.609 --> 00:46:05.156
That's what made me sad.

959
00:46:05.195 --> 00:46:08.195
I think it's because you
didn't cry hard enough.

960
00:46:11.172 --> 00:46:14.687
If you were ripping up your clothes
and were bawling in the waiting room

961
00:46:14.719 --> 00:46:16.836
no one could've made you do it again!

962
00:46:16.906 --> 00:46:18.406
That's true.

963
00:46:19.084 --> 00:46:21.382
It's hard for a human being to say that.

964
00:46:21.445 --> 00:46:24.031
He's so good at breaking up emotions.

965
00:46:25.148 --> 00:46:29.578
I'll make sure bawl even harder,
fiercely and passionately.

966
00:46:29.602 --> 00:46:31.226
They're total best friends.

967
00:46:31.297 --> 00:46:33.390
I can see why she's been so
popular all these years.

968
00:46:33.415 --> 00:46:35.367
She did go up on stage in that situation.

969
00:46:35.383 --> 00:46:37.351
Yeah, she did sing the song again.

970
00:46:37.375 --> 00:46:38.601
Most wouldn't be able to.

971
00:46:38.649 --> 00:46:40.984
The producer would of
course ask her to go again.

972
00:46:41.008 --> 00:46:43.281
"Give it another try."

973
00:46:43.906 --> 00:46:47.328
But a lot of times, if a
singer is famous enough,

974
00:46:47.375 --> 00:46:49.836
would say, "Why would I,"
and not do it again.

975
00:46:49.899 --> 00:46:53.406
The reason I'm best friends with her is

976
00:46:53.430 --> 00:46:55.297
that she did tell me something so cold.

977
00:46:55.328 --> 00:46:58.968
And I sang the song again
while being upset.

978
00:46:58.985 --> 00:47:01.031
But after the song, she was like...

979
00:47:01.056 --> 00:47:04.734
"My princess, you did such a great job!"

980
00:47:04.789 --> 00:47:07.164
I couldn't get mad at her
when she was smiling so big!

981
00:47:07.180 --> 00:47:09.320
She's sane though, right?

982
00:47:12.297 --> 00:47:14.742
- So that's why...
- She's really amazing.

983
00:47:14.851 --> 00:47:15.875
I feel like I was being trained.

984
00:47:15.900 --> 00:47:18.343
How about we hook her up with Jang-hoon?

985
00:47:18.391 --> 00:47:20.398
She's cold-hearted too!
How about with Jang-hoon?

986
00:47:20.460 --> 00:47:21.953
- Is she married?
- She's not.

987
00:47:22.016 --> 00:47:23.664
Should we hook them up?

988
00:47:23.711 --> 00:47:25.562
Isn't she much older then?

989
00:47:25.586 --> 00:47:27.390
No, she was born in 1976.

990
00:47:28.563 --> 00:47:30.539
If she's like that...

991
00:47:30.555 --> 00:47:33.593
I think, though Jang-hoon's retired now,

992
00:47:33.617 --> 00:47:36.351
she might make him play basketball again.

993
00:47:37.851 --> 00:47:40.125
(Wiping away his tears when he retired)

994
00:47:40.156 --> 00:47:41.937
("Let's do it again!")

995
00:47:41.962 --> 00:47:43.562
You should meet her up!

996
00:47:44.291 --> 00:47:46.664
(She might bring him back on the court)

997
00:47:47.073 --> 00:47:49.429
(BoA's questions are done here)

998
00:47:49.727 --> 00:47:52.531
Sang-yeub, it's your last question now.

999
00:47:52.996 --> 00:47:54.742
(In a hurry)

1000
00:47:55.164 --> 00:47:57.234
This time, give us the answer.

1001
00:47:57.258 --> 00:47:58.828
Then we'll guess the question.

1002
00:47:58.882 --> 00:48:00.664
(What a fresh idea!)

1003
00:48:02.708 --> 00:48:04.773
That's creative, right?
It'll make you a star!

1004
00:48:04.820 --> 00:48:06.531
It is a creative idea.

1005
00:48:09.852 --> 00:48:13.375
This was while I was shooting "Give
Love Away," a weekend TV series.

1006
00:48:13.399 --> 00:48:16.351
Park Geun-hyung was my father in the drama.

1007
00:48:16.405 --> 00:48:21.297
Because of him, I got to think
really seriously about acting.

1008
00:48:21.328 --> 00:48:25.982
But he did something specific
for me to think that.

1009
00:48:26.007 --> 00:48:26.898
What do you think he did?

1010
00:48:26.914 --> 00:48:31.297
He did something to change
Sang-yeub into a true actor?

1011
00:48:31.344 --> 00:48:35.328
Yes, it was a pivotal point for me.

1012
00:48:35.391 --> 00:48:39.937
You went to see him in the
waiting room during break time.

1013
00:48:39.977 --> 00:48:44.250
And you found him going over the
script even during break time.

1014
00:48:44.726 --> 00:48:46.273
That's not the answer, but

1015
00:48:46.328 --> 00:48:48.070
he really did do that.

1016
00:48:48.133 --> 00:48:49.562
He seems the type.

1017
00:48:49.602 --> 00:48:51.437
What kind of a scene was it?

1018
00:48:51.462 --> 00:48:53.015
My girlfriend had dumped me.

1019
00:48:53.070 --> 00:48:55.070
I got home drunk in the scene.

1020
00:48:55.086 --> 00:48:58.507
I opened the door and I'm
about to argue with him.

1021
00:48:59.832 --> 00:49:03.330
He did this when I was lost and
couldn't get a hold of my emotions.

1022
00:49:03.355 --> 00:49:08.574
It wasn't in the scripts, but he acted
like your real father and slapped you.

1023
00:49:09.449 --> 00:49:11.471
It's similar, but the
