00:50:35.949 --> 00:50:39.948
I was about to go back to my area
when he said, "You can do better".

1054
00:50:40.215 --> 00:50:44.448
It was so moving when he slapped me
on my back. I'm getting teary now.

1055
00:50:44.472 --> 00:50:46.183
I became very emotional.

1056
00:50:46.340 --> 00:50:48.605
I was only supposed to cry a little bit.

1057
00:50:48.949 --> 00:50:52.472
I was crying so much I
couldn't say my lines.

1058
00:50:52.972 --> 00:50:56.605
His gesture made me let go of
my emotions when I was acting.

1059
00:50:56.918 --> 00:51:00.018
I'm sure Park Geun-hyung hit
you because he was mad.

1060
00:51:00.043 --> 00:51:02.456
- He was frustrated with your acting.
- I won't disagree.

1061
00:51:02.582 --> 00:51:04.245
You kept messing up your lines.

1062
00:51:04.269 --> 00:51:07.550
- He wasn't going to let you get away
with it. - Did it help your acting?

1063
00:51:07.707 --> 00:51:10.975
- It totally helped.
- That's why I keep hitting you.

1064
00:51:11.701 --> 00:51:13.689
(He finally realizes Ho-dong sincerity)

1065
00:51:13.832 --> 00:51:16.589
(Soo-geun receives an abundance
of love from Ho-dong)

1066
00:51:16.793 --> 00:51:19.268
When he was on "Grandpas Over Flowers"...

1067
00:51:19.293 --> 00:51:21.929
he went to go buy uniforms
from soccer teams.

1068
00:51:21.954 --> 00:51:24.796
He said, "This is for
my son and this one is...

1069
00:51:24.821 --> 00:51:27.473
for my other son on our
drama, Sang-yeob".

1070
00:51:28.402 --> 00:51:31.561
This one is for my son on
our drama, Lee Sang-yeob.

1071
00:51:31.785 --> 00:51:34.917
This one is for my youngest
son, Park Sang-won.

1072
00:51:35.511 --> 00:51:37.830
- A son and daughter?
- No, both of them are my sons.

1073
00:51:37.855 --> 00:51:41.683
He bought both uniforms and gave
one to his son and gave one to me.

1074
00:51:42.550 --> 00:51:45.058
He's good about taking
care of his junior actors.

1075
00:51:45.129 --> 00:51:49.152
He did a drama with Dong-hae and
he's still very close to Dong-hae.

1076
00:51:49.316 --> 00:51:51.995
He even came to Super
Junior's concerts as well.

1077
00:51:52.160 --> 00:51:53.777
- He's so cool.
- He's really cool.

1078
00:51:53.879 --> 00:51:58.409
- He's always been great. - He dances
"Sorry, Sorry, Sorry" better than us.

1079
00:52:01.332 --> 00:52:03.886
- I think I went too far.
- Yes, I think so.

1080
00:52:05.496 --> 00:52:08.042
As you all know, Boa and
I acted in the drama...

1081
00:52:08.067 --> 00:52:11.324
"My Wife is Having an
Affair This Week".

1082
00:52:11.637 --> 00:52:16.863
Sung-gyun and I were taken aback
because of what Boa did on the drama.

1083
00:52:17.472 --> 00:52:18.791
- Why?
- Why do you think?

1084
00:52:18.816 --> 00:52:21.213
Why were we taken aback because of Boa?

1085
00:52:21.238 --> 00:52:23.847
She was still hungover
from the previous day?

1086
00:52:23.980 --> 00:52:27.862
- It has something to do with that.
- Just as we thought, it involved alcohol.

1087
00:52:28.176 --> 00:52:29.526
It's got something to do with that.

1088
00:52:29.551 --> 00:52:33.839
They're all seniors and older than Boa,
but when she was on her way home...

1089
00:52:34.410 --> 00:52:36.658
she gave out $100 allowances to them.

1090
00:52:36.683 --> 00:52:38.850
Here you go, use it for your taxi fare.

1091
00:52:39.104 --> 00:52:41.612
- She was drunk. - $100 for everyone.
- No way.

1092
00:52:41.637 --> 00:52:43.260
It happened while she was acting.

1093
00:52:43.285 --> 00:52:45.581
It naturally happened while we were acting.

1094
00:52:45.660 --> 00:52:49.136
I got it! Boa had to act
like she was drunk.

1095
00:52:49.824 --> 00:52:51.933
But she was really drunk.

1096
00:52:52.105 --> 00:52:54.128
I agree with that answer.

1097
00:52:54.347 --> 00:52:57.642
We were taken aback by what she
did while she acted drunk.

1098
00:52:57.667 --> 00:53:01.526
I'm acting. "All of you guys can
go to hell! Get out of my face!"

1099
00:53:02.004 --> 00:53:03.093
Cut!

1100
00:53:03.769 --> 00:53:07.706
"Why are you cutting the scene? Who
the hell are you to yell, 'Cut'?"

1101
00:53:08.902 --> 00:53:11.105
- "Who are you?"
- The scene is over.

1102
00:53:11.246 --> 00:53:13.363
"I'm not done yet, boy!"

1103
00:53:14.199 --> 00:53:17.964
- "Why are you cutting when I'm finally
into it?". - That's what she said.

1104
00:53:18.183 --> 00:53:20.612
All the managers had to come in.

1105
00:53:20.637 --> 00:53:25.878
Boa's manager said, "She's too drunk.
Try the scene when she's sober".

1106
00:53:25.941 --> 00:53:28.738
But they used the scene when she's drunk.

1107
00:53:29.715 --> 00:53:32.760
She tried acting like a fool
during her drunk scene.

1108
00:53:32.785 --> 00:53:34.323
She was too passionate about her acting.

1109
00:53:34.347 --> 00:53:36.890
What was her character's personality like?

1110
00:53:37.230 --> 00:53:41.140
She's a very smart and
uptight divorcee.

1111
00:53:42.480 --> 00:53:44.261
She's a divorcee?

1112
00:53:44.699 --> 00:53:47.898
- A divorcee?
- How did you ever play that character?

1113
00:53:48.144 --> 00:53:49.374
A divorcee!

1114
00:53:51.535 --> 00:53:54.667
I'm going to look over to him
every time you look at me.

1115
00:53:55.129 --> 00:53:58.007
You guys have let him off
too easily these days.

1116
00:53:58.429 --> 00:54:04.003
The character goes and gets drunk, but
comes out of the bar onto a grassy field.

1117
00:54:04.199 --> 00:54:05.554
I got it!

1118
00:54:05.707 --> 00:54:08.835
People were passing by and they
said, "Look, it's Boa" and...

1119
00:54:08.844 --> 00:54:11.682
she yelled back, "What
are you looking at?".

1120
00:54:11.707 --> 00:54:12.707
No, no.

1121
00:54:12.824 --> 00:54:17.511
You were taken aback because of something
I did that wasn't in the script, right?

1122
00:54:17.988 --> 00:54:22.566
She began hitting you guys and
ripping your hair from your head.

1123
00:54:22.722 --> 00:54:24.257
No, no. You're wrong.

1124
00:54:24.504 --> 00:54:26.195
Did she start eating the grass?

1125
00:54:26.363 --> 00:54:30.534
"Let's make green onion pancakes
and eat it since we're drunk".

1126
00:54:30.613 --> 00:54:33.425
- No, no.
- She started to lay down on the grass.

1127
00:54:33.902 --> 00:54:37.158
It wasn't in the script, but
she kept rolling in the grass.

1128
00:54:37.183 --> 00:54:38.886
- You're really close.
- Really?

1129
00:54:38.996 --> 00:54:41.292
Can't you just say that I got it right?

1130
00:54:41.379 --> 00:54:43.425
What did she do on the grass?

1131
00:54:43.769 --> 00:54:45.988
She began taking off her clothes.

1132
00:54:46.074 --> 00:54:48.503
- Not her clothes.
- Her shoes! She took off her shoes.

1133
00:54:48.605 --> 00:54:52.072
- Her shoes. She took off her socks too.
- You got it, Yeong-cheol.

1134
00:54:52.097 --> 00:54:55.261
She took off her socks too. I
believe her socks were the answer.

1135
00:54:55.457 --> 00:54:58.456
Anyone can guess her shoes.
It was her socks. Socks.

1136
00:54:59.246 --> 00:55:01.417
Wait a second. This is so upsetting.

1137
00:55:01.472 --> 00:55:03.924
I'm the one, who guessed she
rolled around the grass.

1138
00:55:03.949 --> 00:55:07.409
- You paved the way for him.
- I even guessed she took off her shoes.

1139
00:55:07.519 --> 00:55:11.526
You need to get the exact word correctly.
It can't be that hard!

1140
00:55:11.551 --> 00:55:14.074
You assisted the best in Korea.

1141
00:55:14.496 --> 00:55:18.527
- Let's move on. - I've always been
the one to put points on the board.

1142
00:55:18.879 --> 00:55:22.120
She was supposed to act drunk and we
were okay with her rolling in the grass.

1143
00:55:22.144 --> 00:55:24.010
We were okay with her taking
off her shoes as well.

1144
00:55:24.035 --> 00:55:26.440
Suddenly, she began taking off her socks.

1145
00:55:26.465 --> 00:55:29.867
- She drank too much.
- Hey, hey! What are you doing?

1146
00:55:30.387 --> 00:55:32.808
Hey, hey! What are you doing?

1147
00:55:32.879 --> 00:55:36.488
- There's people watching you.
- Get up!, you need to get up!

1148
00:55:37.097 --> 00:55:38.460
You scared me!

1149
00:55:38.691 --> 00:55:40.257
You really scared me.

1150
00:55:41.027 --> 00:55:43.916
- You're driving me crazy.
- Why are you taking off your socks?

1151
00:55:43.941 --> 00:55:46.816
- Put it back on.
- Put it in the laundry basket.

1152
00:55:47.691 --> 00:55:49.011
What the heck?

1153
00:55:49.238 --> 00:55:51.635
Were you making up the part
by taking your socks off?

1154
00:55:51.660 --> 00:55:56.159
I made it up on the spot. I had to show,
I was so drunk I thought I was at home.

1155
00:55:56.222 --> 00:55:58.979
I guess you can look back at your
acting by looking back at yourself.

1156
00:55:59.004 --> 00:56:02.152
- You came on our drama as a cameo.
- Wow.

1157
00:56:02.691 --> 00:56:06.253
How detailed was his acting and
did he study for his role?

1158
00:56:06.629 --> 00:56:08.487
He had to turn and look at me in the scene.

1159
00:56:08.512 --> 00:56:13.245
I was supposed to run full-force
at him and turn him around.

1160
00:56:13.722 --> 00:56:16.706
He had to do his look that he always
does when he looks at you. This one.

1161
00:56:16.847 --> 00:56:18.402
Something like this.

1162
00:56:18.504 --> 00:56:21.283
- I was looking right at him and...
- I can imagine it right now.

1163
00:56:21.308 --> 00:56:24.441
I was so surprised. I was only
supposed to say, "You surprised me".

1164
00:56:24.535 --> 00:56:26.627
But instead, I said, "Damn!
You surprised me!".

1165
00:56:26.652 --> 00:56:28.260
It came out naturally.

1166
00:56:28.285 --> 00:56:31.291
It wasn't like regular people
when he grabbed onto my shirt.

1167
00:56:31.316 --> 00:56:34.359
My shirt went up so high,
I was showing my belly.

1168
00:56:35.527 --> 00:56:39.402
It almost felt like he was
lifting me up from my belly.

1169
00:56:39.512 --> 00:56:43.972
Once I felt like that, I didn't know
I was yelling, "Save me! Save me!".

1170
00:56:45.018 --> 00:56:48.683
(He faces off with the man his
wife is having an affair with)

1171
00:56:49.259 --> 00:56:50.273
You scared me!

1172
00:56:50.398 --> 00:56:51.499
(Freaked out)

1173
00:56:51.801 --> 00:56:53.031
Who are you?

1174
00:56:53.363 --> 00:56:54.960
You wanna' fight me?

1175
00:56:55.402 --> 00:56:57.791
- You wanna' fight me?
- Save... Save me.

1176
00:56:57.816 --> 00:56:59.253
It was so fun.

1177
00:56:59.652 --> 00:57:02.980
- He wasn't nervous at all.
- He didn't make any mistakes?

1178
00:57:03.191 --> 00:57:06.635
He didn't make any mistakes, but
I was moved by what he did.

1179
00:57:06.660 --> 00:57:11.699
He did a great job, but he kept asking,
"Should we try again? Let's go again".

1180
00:57:13.426 --> 00:57:15.699
- Let's try that again.
- Why?

1181
00:57:16.324 --> 00:57:18.339
I don't like what I did.

1182
00:57:18.504 --> 00:57:20.628
I didn't have many lines.

1183
00:57:21.902 --> 00:57:25.769
Shouldn't I have more lines since
I began my career in dramas?

1184
00:57:26.081 --> 00:57:28.058
He's telling us a moving story.

1185
00:57:28.410 --> 00:57:30.714
Do you think he can keep acting?

1186
00:57:30.863 --> 00:57:34.479
I'm looking forward to Ma Dong-seok
and Ho-dong in a shot together.

1187
00:57:34.504 --> 00:57:37.277
You could be like Jang
Chen from "The Outlaws".

1188
00:57:37.426 --> 00:57:39.080
You can be on "The Outlaws II".

1189
00:57:39.105 --> 00:57:41.972
- He could be Jang Chen!
- Yeah, Dong Chen.

1190
00:57:42.355 --> 00:57:45.166
- You'd be the new gangster boss.
- Dong Chen.

1191
00:57:45.191 --> 00:57:47.339
Did you come here by yourself?

1192
00:57:47.738 --> 00:57:49.189
Did you come here by yourself?

1193
00:57:49.323 --> 00:57:53.034
Are you Ma Dong-seok? Wanna' come
over and hang out over here?

1194
00:57:53.207 --> 00:57:54.704
Hang out here?

1195
00:57:54.871 --> 00:57:57.816
Hey, you! I'll be waiting for you here!

1196
00:57:58.347 --> 00:57:59.831
I'm waiting, right here.

1197
00:57:59.972 --> 00:58:02.269
Let's go, me and you! One-on-one.

1198
00:58:02.465 --> 00:58:04.673
He looks like he can play the part.

1199
00:58:04.926 --> 00:58:06.063
Good job, Sang-yeob!

1200
00:58:06.088 --> 00:58:08.689
(We'll look forward to Ma Dong-seok
and Kang Ho-dong's "The Outlaws 2")

1201
00:58:08.714 --> 00:58:11.821
(Are you still looking for your true love?)

1202
00:58:12.251 --> 00:58:14.493
(We'll find your true love today)

1203
00:58:14.687 --> 00:58:17.059
(Let's get married)

1204
00:58:17.730 --> 00:58:21.684
(Let's look for your one
and only love here)

1205
00:58:22.965 --> 00:58:26.017
- Seriously?
- What the heck? Why aren't there any guys?

1206
00:58:26.042 --> 00:58:28.926
How come guys are so rude?
Do you know what time it is?

1207
00:58:28.951 --> 00:58:32.027
- How come we're here first?
- I think our seats are here. - There?

1208
00:58:32.105 --> 00:58:35.025
- There's three seats here. Do you want
dried squid? - Yeah, it looks good.

1209
00:58:35.051 --> 00:58:37.550
I was Miss Squid of Ulsan.

1210
00:58:37.832 --> 00:58:39.477
Doesn't it look good on me?

1211
00:58:39.519 --> 00:58:43.111
I need to find my true love. Do you
think I'll find him? I hope so.

1212
00:58:43.137 --> 00:58:44.682
I heard this place was famous.

1213
00:58:44.707 --> 00:58:49.159
You guys are bringing down the quality
here. You guys are really ugly.

1214
00:58:49.379 --> 00:58:52.088
You're uglier. What's with
your country-bumpkin outfit?

1215
00:58:52.113 --> 00:58:54.869
What are you talking about? Why
do you think you're prettier?

1216
00:58:54.894 --> 00:58:56.978
Didn't you guys see "Hyo-ri's Home Stay"?

1217
00:58:57.004 --> 00:58:59.885
- Why? What's on the show?
- I'm IU's little sister.

1218
00:58:59.910 --> 00:59:02.183
- What's your name?
- Ahni U.

1219
00:59:03.051 --> 00:59:07.915
Yeah, right. Wait a second. Why are you
copying me, wearing black and white?

1220
00:59:08.597 --> 00:59:11.230
- I'm so upset.
- You're copying me, aren't you?

1221
00:59:11.379 --> 00:59:13.135
You're the one, who copied me.

1222
00:59:13.160 --> 00:59:16.292
This place must be losing
its touch as well.

1223
00:59:16.465 --> 00:59:18.518
There isn't another place
like this in the world.

1224
00:59:18.543 --> 00:59:21.159
- Is this where we're supposed to be?
- Yeah.

1225
00:59:21.183 --> 00:59:23.236
Isn't this the place we're
supposed to meet them?

1226
00:59:23.262 --> 00:59:26.340
- My goodness!
- Are you guys the ladies we're meeting?

1227
00:59:26.637 --> 00:59:30.020
- Those four are pretty good-looking.
- Is that Kevin?

1228
00:59:30.207 --> 00:59:32.644
What's with that giant?

1229
00:59:33.964 --> 00:59:35.481
What's he doing?

1230
00:59:35.816 --> 00:59:37.403
He smells a bit odd.

1231
00:59:38.683 --> 00:59:41.846
- Is this a horror movie?
- You're too much. - It's "Misery"!

1232
00:59:41.871 --> 00:59:46.441
(You leave me after
waking me up from sleep)

1233
00:59:47.456 --> 00:59:49.753
- You're too much.
- It's "Misery"!

1234
00:59:49.918 --> 00:59:50.918
My gosh!

1235
00:59:51.816 --> 00:59:55.025
How can you spray water at me
when you've never met me before!

1236
00:59:55.050 --> 00:59:56.822
I mistook you for a real flower.

1237
00:59:56.847 --> 01:00:00.908
- Don't water me, I might grow taller.
- Stop, you're getting the squid wet.

1238
01:00:00.933 --> 01:00:02.916
Is this where we're supposed to be seating?

1239
01:00:02.941 --> 01:00:05.839
You shouldn't fight when
it's a beautiful day.

1240
01:00:06.582 --> 01:00:10.825
It's such a cold day that even angels
in heaven might catch a cold. Ah-choo.

1241
01:00:10.957 --> 01:00:14.605
I came to meet a woman, who will
warm my heart like citron tea.

1242
01:00:14.660 --> 01:00:19.347
- Did he get that hat transplanted on
his head? - Where? Where could you be?

